## Writer-QA pairing rules

The writer and QA panel are always different perspectives.
A lesson written by the Staff Engineer PM is QA'd partly by the
Junior PM Reader — because the engineer's blind spot is always
"is this actually followable by someone without my background?"

| Writer persona | Always includes in QA panel |
|---|---|
| staff-engineer-pm | Junior PM Reader (mandatory) |
| senior-pm | Staff Engineer (keeps it honest on tech claims) |
| cfo-finance | GTM Lead (catches when finance ignores distribution) |
| gtm-lead | CFO/Finance Lead (catches when growth ignores margin) |

This cross-pairing is enforced in the lesson manifest.
The QA skill reads the manifest to know which panel to assemble —
it does not rely on tags alone when a writer is declared.
